m_q.target_metric: Percentage of samples that failed to meet the swimming standard (Enterococcus > 104) at Boston Harbor beaches that had rainfall within 24 hours prior to sampling.
sub_questions: Identify samples that failed to meet the swimming standard (Enterococcus > 104).
Determine if there was rainfall within 24 hours prior to each failed sample.
Calculate the percentage of failed samples with rainfall.

format_notes: Some files have different numbers of Enterococcus columns (e.g., Enterococcus, Enterococcus.1, Enterococcus.2, Enterococcus.3).
The 'Tag' columns may contain '<' characters indicating values below a detection limit. These should be handled appropriately (e.g., imputing with a small value or filtering).
The boston-harbor-beaches.txt file uses comma as a delimiter.

constraints: Enterococcus values must be numeric and greater than 0.
1-Day Rain values must be numeric and greater than or equal to 0.
